# Version bump after CSS/JS changes (required every time)

**Whenever you change any file under `site/assets/css/` or `site/assets/js/`, you MUST in the same response also update `site/index.html`:** bump the cache-busting `?v=` and keep CSS and JS in sync.

1. In `site/index.html`, replace the current version with a new value (e.g. `2.0.3` → `2.0.4`) in **all three** places:
   - `link rel="preload"` for `styles.min.css`
   - `link rel="stylesheet"` for `styles.min.css`
   - `script src` for `script.min.js`
2. Use the **same** version string for all three. One version for both CSS and JS.
3. Do this for every CSS or JS change, whether you touched only one file or both.

Minification is done on the backend (CI/deploy). Do not run `npm run build` in this workflow.
